---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="For Creators — Protect Your Work From AI" description="Your creative work may have been used to train AI without permission. Learn your rights, protect your content, and understand your legal options.">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-900 via-blue-800 to-slate-900 py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-amber-400/20 text-amber-300 text-sm font-semibold rounded-full mb-4">For Creators</span>
      <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-white leading-tight mb-6">
        Your Work Was Used to Train AI.<br/>
        <span class="text-amber-400">Here's What You Can Do.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-blue-100 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-8">
        Billions of images, articles, books, and songs were scraped from the internet to train AI models — without asking the people who made them. If that includes your work, you have real options.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="#protect" class="px-6 py-3 bg-amber-400 text-slate-900 font-bold rounded-xl hover:bg-amber-300 transition-colors">Protect My Work →</a>
        <a href="#rights" class="px-6 py-3 bg-white/10 text-white font-semibold rounded-xl border border-white/20 hover:bg-white/20 transition-colors">Know My Rights</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 1: Understand Your Rights -->
  <section id="rights" class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-text mb-8">Understand Your Rights</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-3">⚖️</div>
        <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-lg text-text mb-2">AI Training Is Not Always Fair Use</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">The U.S. Copyright Office confirmed that using copyrighted works to train AI that generates competing content goes beyond fair use.</p>
        <a href="/blog/copyright-office-part-3" class="text-primary text-sm font-semibold hover:underline">Read the analysis →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-3">💰</div>
        <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-lg text-text mb-2">Creators Are Winning</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">Anthropic offered $1.5 billion to settle with 500,000 authors. Getty Images is suing Stability AI. The tide is turning.</p>
        <a href="/cases" class="text-primary text-sm font-semibold hover:underline">See all cases →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-3">🎨</div>
        <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-lg text-text mb-2">AI-Assisted Work CAN Be Copyrighted</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">If you use AI as a tool but add substantial human creativity, your work may still qualify for copyright protection.</p>
        <a href="/learn/can-you-copyright-ai-content" class="text-primary text-sm font-semibold hover:underline">Learn how →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-3">🌍</div>
        <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-lg text-text mb-2">Laws Vary by Country</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">The US requires human authorship. The UK has different rules. Japan is AI-friendly. Know what applies to you.</p>
        <a href="/laws" class="text-primary text-sm font-semibold hover:underline">Compare laws →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Protect Your Work -->
  <section id="protect" class="bg-slate-50 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-text mb-3">Protect Your Work From AI Scraping</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted mb-8">Take action now to prevent AI companies from using your content for training.</p>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <a href="/tools/robots-txt-ai-blocker" class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-5 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow group">
          <div class="text-3xl">🤖</div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-text group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">Block AI Crawlers (Free Tool)</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mt-1">Generate a robots.txt that blocks GPTBot, ClaudeBot, and 15+ other AI crawlers from your site.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="text-primary font-semibold text-sm shrink-0">Use Tool →</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/tools/ai-copyright-checker" class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-5 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow group">
          <div class="text-3xl">⚖️</div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-text group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">Check Your Copyright Risk</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mt-1">Answer 6 questions to understand if your AI-assisted work is copyrightable.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="text-primary font-semibold text-sm shrink-0">Take Quiz →</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/learn/protect-content-from-ai" class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-5 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow group">
          <div class="text-3xl">🛡️</div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-text group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">Full Protection Guide</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mt-1">Complete guide: robots.txt, meta tags, HTTP headers, opt-out programs, and legal measures.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="text-primary font-semibold text-sm shrink-0">Read Guide →</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: Cases -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-text mb-3">Creators Fighting Back</h2>
    <p class="text-text-muted mb-8">These cases are shaping the future of AI copyright law.</p>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-5">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-amber-50 text-amber-700 text-xs font-semibold rounded">Settlement</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-text-muted">$1.5 Billion</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-text">Authors v. Anthropic</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mt-1">500,000 authors sued over books used to train Claude. Largest copyright settlement offer in history.</p>
        <a href="/cases/authors-v-anthropic" class="text-primary text-sm font-semibold hover:underline mt-2 inline-block">Full case details →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-5">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-green-50 text-green-700 text-xs font-semibold rounded">Active</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-text-muted">12 million images</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-text">Getty Images v. Stability AI</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mt-1">Getty alleges Stable Diffusion was trained on 12 million copyrighted photos without license.</p>
        <a href="/cases/getty-v-stability-ai" class="text-primary text-sm font-semibold hover:underline mt-2 inline-block">Full case details →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-5">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-green-50 text-green-700 text-xs font-semibold rounded">Active</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-text-muted">Billions at stake</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-text">New York Times v. OpenAI</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mt-1">NYT alleges millions of articles used to train ChatGPT, creating a competing product.</p>
        <a href="/cases/nyt-v-openai" class="text-primary text-sm font-semibold hover:underline mt-2 inline-block">Full case details →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <a href="/cases" class="inline-block mt-6 text-primary font-semibold hover:underline">View all cases →</a>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: Guides -->
  <section class="bg-slate-50 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-text mb-8">Essential Guides for Creators</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href="/learn/who-owns-ai-generated-art" class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-5 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-text mb-1">Who Owns AI-Generated Art?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">If you typed the prompt, do you own the image? It depends.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/learn/can-you-copyright-ai-content" class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-5 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-text mb-1">Can You Copyright AI Content?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">The spectrum from "no protection" to "fully copyrightable."</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/learn/ai-training-fair-use" class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-5 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-text mb-1">AI Training & Fair Use</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">When can AI companies legally use your work?</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/learn/ai-copyright-basics" class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-5 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-text mb-1">AI Copyright Basics</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">New to this? Start here for a plain-English overview.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Newsletter -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-blue-100 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-text mb-2">Get Updates When Creators Win</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-5">Weekly digest of rulings, settlements, and new protections for creators.</p>
      <form class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 max-w-md mx-auto">
        <input type="email" placeholder="your@email.com" class="flex-1 px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-300 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary" />
        <button type="submit" class="px-6 py-3 bg-primary text-white font-semibold rounded-xl hover:bg-primary-dark transition-colors">Subscribe Free</button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
